Pet poofing on LD is annoying. All that mana/med time to recover: lost.<br>
<br>
I think it has to be that way. <br>
<br>
It's one thing to have an inventory no rent item stay for 30 miniutes. It's on your person, included in your save file. The pet is external and once your connection to it is severed (like having it charmed, as well as going LD) you can't get it back.<br>
<br>
It's also not much fun for your bard and wizard friends using AoE and getting aggro'ed by your now NPC pet. My 51 pet nearly killed a 52 bard and 53 cleric when I went LD while the bard was playing some song the pet didn't like. They only survived because the pet poofed (we had just finished a fight so they were low HP and mana).<br>
