<br>
1) Server has to track all pets - News flash. All world servers are made up of 20 or so individual machines. Each zone itself is an independant 'program' running on a rather powerfull machine. Now, how many zones are there? 200ish? That's 10 zones per server, and (if populations were divided equally amungst them), about 200 people per individual machine (assuming 4000 players on that world server at peak times). That's a max of 200 pets, and probably closer to 30-40 pets of the Mage variety, on an Individual machine. (Numbers approximate and assumed)<br>
<br>
Basically, this is not a case of 1 machine, loaded down with all of EQ's server software, having to track 3-400 pets all at once. It's quite a bit lighter a load than that. There's tons more NPC casters casting spells than there are MAGE pets wanting to cast a Damage shield on themselves.<br>
<br>
2) Resources are limited to let pets cast instantly on summon - Oddly, the only pets that have issues with summoning a DS on summon are the same pets that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> never</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> recast their damage shield again. The pet that causes more server resources to be taken up (post-50 fire pet) casts it's spells immediately, and often, making sure it's fully buffed up according to it's spell set.<br>
<br>
If they're so concerned with resources for casters, here's a few hints. (a) Let NPC cast buff spells last 2x normal duration. Decrease the need for the NPC's to cast in half. PC pets remain at normal duration, or not. They recast immediately anyways. (b) Increase the time it takes for mobs to buff themselves. Casting mobs outnumber Magepets by 5x easily, and with the new casting rules, now buff 'friend' mobs as well as themselves.<br>
<br>
Actual resources saved by forbidding magepets to instabuff themselves is minimal at best.<br>
<br>
Only reason I can think of for this is, it's either a bug, or it's an insanely stupid limit put in during ages past because they felt the pets instabuffing themselves was too powerfull, and they're just too darn lame to say it (or, even more likely, don't even know anymore why it is intentionally that way). <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
