Not that I necessarily agree that this is the only reason for sluggish buffing, but if you give it some thought, it certainly doesn't seem all that hard to believe.  For every one player-made pet, how many NPC pets with buffs (and NPCs with buffs, for that matter) do you think exist in the game world?  The servers have to manage those, too.<br>
<br>
The entire act of checking every single NPC and NPC/PC pet that is alive at time X, what buffs they have, what buffs they're missing, what class they are (and thus what buffs they have access to cast), and whether they should refresh any buffs probably is rather resource intensive.  If they made this check every second of every minute... well, you can probably see how resources can start to add up.  Logically, you space these checks out to balance the load.<br>
<br>
I think that as much as we'd like to believe that there isn't any limit to what can be done within EQ, the reality is that there are still some technical restrictions that stand in the way (even if they do seem rather minor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p><font face="Verdana">
